<h2>Chapter 4: Statistical Inference</h2>

<h3>Sampling Methods</h3>
<p>Select representative data from a population (Random, Stratified, Systematic).</p>

<h3>Confidence Intervals</h3>
<p>Estimate population parameters with a given confidence level.</p>

<h3>Sample Size Determination</h3>
<p>Calculate how much data is needed for accurate results.</p>

<h3>Hypothesis Testing</h3>
<p>Decision-making process using sample data to accept or reject a hypothesis.</p>

<h3>Z-test & t-test</h3>
<p>Tests used to compare sample and population means.</p>

